headlines.description: — Joel Embiid made his closing argument for MVP votes and all but wrapped up the NBA scoring title, scoring 41 points while adding 20 rebounds and four assists to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 133-120 victory Saturday over the Indiana Pacers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 41 points, 20 rebounds as Sixers down Pacers

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 21 points and nine assists in his return from soreness in his right knee, Dillon Brooks scored 23 points and the Memphis Grizzlies routed the New Orleans Pelicans 141-114 on Saturday night to tie the 2012-13 franchise record for...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant returns to help Grizzlies rout Pelicans, 141-114

events.name: Golden State Warriors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jonathan Kuminga and Jordan Poole each had 18 points and the Golden State Warriors won their fourth straight, beating the San Antonio Spurs 100-94 on Saturday night to strengthen their hopes for a top-three seed despite being without Stephen Curry...
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors hold off Spurs and maintain hold on third seed

headlines.description: — Paul George put the Western Conference on notice that he is ready for the play-in tournament, and hopefully beyond.
headlines.shortLinkText: George leads Clippers past Kings for 4th straight victory
